<DOC><DOCNO> AP880301-0279 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-01-88 1615EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Unilever     03-01 0207</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Unilever,0215</SECOND><HEAD>Net Profit Flat at Consumer Product Giant</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Unilever, the Anglo-Dutch home products giant,reported Tuesday that its fourth-quarter net profit was flat asrevenue slipped a bit.   The company, which is made up of Unilever PLC of Britain andUnilever NV of the Netherlands, said its after-tax profit wasunchanged at 186 million pounds, which is the equivalent of about$331 million. Sales dipped 0.7 percent to 4.45 billion pounds, orabout $7.92 billion, from 4.48 billion pounds.   Unilever said pre-tax profit on its North American activitiesdoubled to the equivalent of $178 million.   For all of 1987, Unilever reported a net profit of 756 millionpounds, or about $1.35 billion. That was up 14 percent fromearnings of 664 million pounds the previous year.   Sales for the year fell 3 percent to 16.55 billion pounds, orabout $29.5 billion, from 17.14 billion pounds in 1986.   Pre-tax profit on North American activities also doubled for theyear, rising to the equivalent of $425 million.   Unilever said that for the full year, sales gains were recordedin most product groups and substantial contributions were made byrecent acquisitions, including the U.S.-based Chesebrough-Pond'sInc., which was purchased in December 1986 for $3.15 billion.</TEXT></DOC>